---

### 2. `.gitignore`
Even if you aren't using a package manager right now, it is a best practice to include a `.gitignore` file. This prevents your operating system or code editor from accidentally uploading hidden configuration files to GitHub.

```text
# OS generated files
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db

# IDE and Editor folders
.vscode/
.idea/
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?

# Ignore node_modules if you ever decide to install Tailwind locally in the future
node_modules/
npm-debug.log
yarn-error.log
